The fiber metric on $\Lambda^k T^* M$ requested in Problem 2-16 below is built pointwise first. The following sequence carries out the linear algebra on a single inner product space $V$; the fibers of $\Lambda^k T^*M$ are the spaces of alternating $k$-tensors on the tangent spaces $T_pM$, each of which carries the inner product $g_p$.

Throughout, $V$ is a finite-dimensional real inner product space, $k \ge 1$, and $\Lambda^k(V^*)$ denotes the space of alternating $k$-tensors on $V$. For a covector $a \in V^*$ we write $a^\sharp$ for its Riesz representative, the unique vector with $\langle a^\sharp, \cdot\rangle = a$, and we equip $V^*$ with the inner product
\begin{equation}
\langle a, b \rangle = \langle a^\sharp, b^\sharp \rangle, \tag{2.26a}
\end{equation}
which is the coordinate-free form of Lee's $g^{ij}a_i b_j$.

