Let $(M, g)$ be a Riemannian manifold.
\begin{enumerate}
\item[(a)] If $M$ is isotropic at one point and it is homogeneous, then it is isotropic.
\item[(b)] If $M$ is frame-homogeneous, then it is homogeneous and isotropic.
\end{enumerate}

