\uses{ex:semidirect-products}
Verify that $N \rtimes_\theta H$ is indeed a Lie group with the multiplication defined above, and with $(e,e)$ identity and $(n,h)^{-1} = (\theta_{h^{-1}}(n^{-1}),h^{-1})$.
